questions.scenario:
You are debugging a production issue where a `HashMap` is used to cache JPA entities within a `@Transactional` Spring Service. The service performs the following logic: 

java
@Transactional
public void syncUser(UserDTO dto) {
    User user = new User(dto.getName()); // ID is null initially
    Map<User, String> processingMap = new HashMap<>();
    processingMap.put(user, "PENDING");

    userRepository.saveAndFlush(user); // ID is generated here via Identity strategy

    if (!processingMap.containsKey(user)) {
        throw new IllegalStateException("User lost in map!");
    }
}

Users report that the `IllegalStateException` is sporadically thrown even though the `user` object reference has not changed.
